  "prompt": "How do you find out the status of an SFSU application?",
  "response": "To check the status of your San Francisco State University (SFSU) application, follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Log in to your SF State Gateway Account:**\n   - Visit the [SF State Gateway](https://gateway.sfsu.edu/) portal.\n   - Enter your username (SF State ID) and password. If you haven\u2019t set up your account yet, follow the instructions to activate it using the information provided in your application acknowledgment email.\n\n### 2. **Check Application Status:**\n   - Once logged in, navigate to the \"Student Center\" or \"Application Status\" section.\n   - Look for your application status, which will indicate whether it is complete, under review, or a decision has been made.\n\n### 3. **Check Email for Updates:**\n   - SFSU often sends application updates and decisions via email. Ensure you\u2019re monitoring the email address you provided in your application, including your spam/junk folder.\n\n### 4. **Contact the Admissions Office (if necessary):**\n   - If you\u2019re unable to find your application status or have questions, contact the SFSU Office of Admissions:\n     - **Phone:** (415) 338-6486\n     - **Email:** ugadm@sfsu.edu\n     - **Website:** [SFSU Admissions](https://admit.sfsu.edu/)\n\n### 5. **Check Supporting Document Status (if applicable):**\n   - If you\u2019re required to submit additional documents (e.g., transcripts, test scores), ensure they\u2019ve been received and processed. You can verify this in your Gateway account or by contacting the admissions office.\n\nMake sure to check your application status regularly for updates and follow any instructions sent by the university.",
